    policy_id INT,
    claim_amount DECIMAL,
    status VARCHAR(20)
);

    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50)

    policyholder_id INT,
    policy_type VARCHAR(50),
    policy_amount DECIMAL
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50)
);

    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
);

    claim_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    policy_id INT,
    claim_amount DECIMAL,
    status VARCHAR(20)
);</t><s>SELECT name, policy_type, phone_number FROM policyholders, policies, agents WHERE policies.policyholder_id = policyholders.id AND agents.agent_id = policies.policyholder_id;</s>

    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50)
);

    agent_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
);

    policy_id INT,

    status VARCHAR(20)

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><s>select * from customers</s>

CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><s>select id, name, email, phone from customers</s>

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Customers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))</t><s>select id, name, region, agent_id from agency</s>

CREATE TABLE Agents (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><s>SELECT Customers.name, Policies.policy_number, Claims.claim_number FROM Customers JOIN Policies ON Customers.id = Policies.customer_id JOIN Claims ON Customers.id = Claims.customer_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Customers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><s>select customers.name, policies.policy_number, claims.claim_number from customers join policies on customers.id = policies.customer_id join claims on customers.id = claims.customer_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))</t><s>SELECT Customers.name, Policies.policy_number, Claims.claim_number FROM Customers JOIN Policies ON Customers.id = Policies.customer_id JOIN Claims ON Customers.id = Claims.customer_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

<t>CREATE TABLE Agents (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Customers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))</t><s>select customers.name, policies.policy_number, claims.claim_number from customers join policies on customers.id = policies.customer_id join claims on customers.id = claims.customer_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Agents (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))

CREATE TABLE Customers (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)</t><s>SELECT Customers.name, Policies.policy_number, Claims.claim_number FROM Customers JOIN Policies ON Customers.id = Policies.customer_id JOIN Claims ON Customers.id = Claims.customer_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Agents (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, email STRING, phone STRING)

<t>CREATE TABLE Agency (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, region STRING, agent_id INT REFERENCES Agents(id))

CREATE TABLE Claims (id INT PRIMARY KEY, claim_number STRING, date DATE, amount FLOAT, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))

CREATE TABLE Policies (id INT PRIMARY KEY, policy_number STRING, policy_type STRING, customer_id INT REFERENCES Customers(id))
